Toco Dance Club was a traditional nightclub in Sao Paulo. It opened its doors in 1972 and ended its activities in 1997. It was located on the east side of São Paulo and had a capacity of over four thousand people. Your sound system and lights was undisputed reference.

The Toco tops which can be considered as a sort of triad unforgettable Paulista clubs alongside Overnight Hand and Counter In so dear, various celebrations of the three houses were made extinct in the 2000s.

Since the late '90s, with the closure of the house, the property number 509 Dona Matilde street in the neighborhood of Vila Matilde, gives way to a bingo. On the evening of June 23, 2007 a ​​party marked the re-opening of the nightclub, now under the name Space Datoko. According to organizers, with a packed house, over a thousand people were left out of the party.
